text_blocks.text:
The responsibility for the implementation of the plan is that of the Ministry for State for Special Programmes in conjunction with National Disaster Operation Centre. There will be an established system providing operational concepts and procedures associated with day-to-day operational response to emergencies by respective departments when disaster strikes. This will contain hazard specific and departmental or thematic contingency plans and emergency procedures in the event of a disaster, providing for:•
* The allocation of responsibilities to the various role players and coordination in the carrying out of those responsibilities;
* Effective early warning linked to early response and relief;
* Early recovery linked to longer-term development after disaster.
